President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the inauguration of His Excellency Hakainde Hichilema in Zambia on August 24, 2021. The delegation will be led by Ms. Enoh T. Ebong, Acting Director of the United States Trade and Development Agency. Other members of the delegation include Mr. David J. Young, Chargé d’Affaires, ad interim, U.S. Embassy Lusaka, and Ms. Dana L. Banks, Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for Africa.